HEADWORD: Air sac
<hw>Air" sac`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>One of the spaces in different parts of the bodies of birds, which
are filled with air and connected with the air passages of the lungs; an
air cell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An <er>alveolus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>airscrew</ent>⟦br⟧
